# Honcho Inspector backend environment file.
#
# This file is sourced by the launcher (`/usr/local/bin/honcho-inspector`)
# and by the systemd unit (EnvironmentFile=) to override defaults.
# Mode is 0640 root:www-data so the service user can read it but other
# users cannot.
#
# The two required values are listed below. Set HONCHO_CRYPTO_KEY to a
# stable secret; if it changes, every encrypted profile API key in the
# database becomes unreadable. Generate one with:
#
#   openssl rand -base64 32
#
# HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_USERNAME / HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD are
# OPTIONAL. Set both on a fresh install to have AdminBootstrap create
# the first admin on startup; leave blank and use the UI first-run
# wizard or the emergency CLI instead.

#HONCHO_CRYPTO_KEY=
#HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_USERNAME=
#HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
#HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_FIRSTNAME=
#HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_LASTNAME=
#HONCHO_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_EMAIL=